Nov 21, 2013
Joe B

        rated it
        it was amazing



 Do you like action, intense moments and a story that keeps you reading? Well if you do, I have the book for you, Zach’s Lie By Roland Smith.  I give this book a 5 out of 5 stars and would recommend it to a friend because I love the action in the book and that there is always something new in every chapter.  Here is an action moment in the book. “I woke up with a hand clamped over my mouth, a man telling me make one sound and you will die.” That is from the part of the book when the bad guys bre
	Do you like action, intense moments and a story that keeps you reading? Well if you do, I have the book for you, Zach’s Lie By Roland Smith. 	I give this book a 5 out of 5 stars and would recommend it to a friend because I love the action in the book and that there is always something new in every chapter. 	Here is an action moment in the book. “I woke up with a hand clamped over my mouth, a man telling me make one sound and you will die.” That is from the part of the book when the bad guys break into Jack’s house looking for his father. The men start talking to him and ask him where is your father, we need to talk to him. Jack, his sister and mom sit there clueless wondering why these men would need to talk to their husband/father. Then the men tell the mother that the phone will ring, the men will answer it and then the mother will say “they will kill us if you talk.” That is one of first exciting action parts in the book but there are many more.	Mostly every chapter in the book has a different topic. In some parts of the book, things change like a snap of the fingers. First is the day after the men break into their house. The police come swarming in and take almost everything they own to try to use it as evidence against their father. Then in the next chapter, they’re stuck in a hotel and can’t leave for the next 4 days. After that chapter, things heat up with the D.E.A telling them that they have to change their identities and move far away. It takes the mom and sister a few days to feel okay with such a life changing decision but with Jack he doesn’t want to leave. His Mom and sister got to pick their names but the D.E.A. gave Jack the name Zach, which he didn’t like. 	If you want to find out what else happens to the new Granger Family and all the action ahead in the book, I recommend you give this book a try. Trust me when I say that Zach’s Lie will never disappoint you and it definitely won’t be a book that you don’t finish because once you get on board, it is a one- way ticket to the end.
...more






