First off: I'm nobodies mother.That being said, I have some opinions on this book that contradict the things others have said. I read this series in grade 7. Not because it was mandatory, I just picked it up at the library one day. I haven't read them since but I remember that I thought they were kick booty (because back then I couldn't say 'ass'). Let me tell you why....That was the year that my dad got cancer. Things were really tough in my house. I just took to curling up with a book when I wanted to cry. The land of books is the best for escape, especially action stories. A straightforward tale full of bad guys and excitement is sometimes the best medicine.Now, as a more educated reader, I can say no, it was not the most educational read. What can i say? Kids aren't the best critics. But these stories still hold a special place in my heart.
