(Spoilers) Loved it!!! Zach is actually Jack; he's in the witness security program. Alonzo and his PIC's (partners ib crime) search for Zach to find a journal that will give him a key to Zach's dad's cell. Zach's dad was an airplane pilot and has something to do with a drug cartel. He moves to a small town in Elko, Neveda and meets a strange janitor that becomes a close a friend. His name is Sam. Sam is actually a spy, (CIA material, but a different agency) who proves his skills in the end. But at Zach's new school, Peter Short become more than a bully, he becomes a problem; he tells Alonzo and his crew where and who Zach really is. Zach ends up moving again and HAS to change his name, so he chooses Mack, short for Mackenzie. Truly worth my friends recommending it to me.
